<geoCoordinate id="17D5502B2439BD60FD72D88B1809A5E2" box="[722,822,1737,1763]" degrees="10" direction="north" minutes="15" orientation="latitude" pageId="39" pageNumber="40" precision="925" value="10.25">10°15’N</geoCoordinate>
and 68°28’– 
<geoCoordinate id="17D5502B2439BD60FC75D88B1F7DA5E2" box="[981,1090,1737,1763]" degrees="68" direction="west" minutes="37" orientation="longitude" pageId="39" pageNumber="40" precision="925" value="-68.61667">68°37’W</geoCoordinate>
in the Coastal Cordillera in 
<collectingCountry id="0AF6767C2439BD60FF37D8B21A30A40B" box="[151,271,1776,1802]" name="Venezuela" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">Venezuela</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingRegion id="B025F80E2439BD60FEBED8B21ABAA40B" box="[286,389,1776,1802]" country="Venezuela" name="Yaracuy" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">Yaracuy</collectingRegion>
), at 1192(
<date id="065F102C2439BD60FE59D8B21941A40B" box="[505,638,1776,1802]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40" value="1045" valueMax="1300">1045–1300</date>
) m elevation in montane rainforest (
<figureCitation id="EADA2A692439BD60FB89D8B21FBEA40B" box="[1065,1153,1776,1802]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="40.[159,269,1195,1218]" captionTargetBox="[170,1417,161,1170]" captionTargetId="figure@40.[151,1436,141,1190]" captionTargetPageId="40" captionText="FIGURE 10. Distribution maps of Geonoma braunii, G. brenesii, G. brongniartii subsp. brongniartii, and G. brongniartii subsp. pascoensis." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3538382" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3538382/files/figure.png" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">Fig. 10</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="725E36EC2439BD60FF66D9541E72A456" blockId="39.[151,1437,693,1957]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">
<emphasis id="4095EAFE2439BD60FF66D9541AFDA431" bold="true" box="[198,450,1814,1840]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">Taxonomic notes:—</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="16704B1D2439BD60FE63D9541945A431" author="Stauffer, F." box="[451,634,1814,1840]" journalOrPublisher="Acta Botanica Venezuelica" pageId="39" pageNumber="40" pagination="1 - 10" part="20" refId="ref124409" refString="Stauffer, F. (1997) Estudio morfologico y taxonomico de Geonoma spinescens H. Wendl. ex Burret (Arecaceae) y descripcion de una nueva variedad. Acta Botanica Venezuelica 20: 1 - 10." title="Estudio morfologico y taxonomico de Geonoma spinescens H. Wendl. ex Burret (Arecaceae) y descripcion de una nueva variedad" type="journal article" year="1997">Stauffer (1997)</bibRefCitation>
recognized this species as a variety of 
<taxonomicName id="B5E14D6F2439BD60FBFFD9541E66A430" authorityName="Wendland ex Burret" authorityYear="1930" box="[1119,1369,1814,1841]" class="Liliopsida" family="Arecaceae" genus="Geonoma" kingdom="Plantae" order="Arecales" pageId="39" pageNumber="40" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="spinescens">
<emphasis id="4095EAFE2439BD60FBFFD9541E66A430" box="[1119,1369,1814,1841]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">Geonoma spinescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. It is here recognized at the species level, differing from 
<taxonomicName id="B5E14D6F2439BD60FD51D97F18B1A459" authorityName="Wendland ex Burret" authorityYear="1930" box="[753,910,1853,1880]" class="Liliopsida" family="Arecaceae" genus="Geonoma" kingdom="Plantae" order="Arecales" pageId="39" pageNumber="40" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="spinescens">
<emphasis id="4095EAFE2439BD60FD51D97F18B1A459" box="[753,910,1853,1880]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">G. spinescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in its alternately arranged flower pits.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="725E36EC2439BD60FF66D92619A7A4A4" blockId="39.[151,1437,693,1957]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">
<emphasis id="4095EAFE2439BD60FF66D9261ACAA47F" bold="true" box="[198,501,1892,1918]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">Subspecific variation:—</emphasis>
Three traits (stem branching, stem 
<typeStatus id="AD5A884E2439BD60FC35D92618F5A47F" box="[917,970,1892,1918]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">type</typeStatus>
, leaf division) vary within this species, but all specimens come from the same area.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
